          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between a Company Page and a personal profile?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Personal profiles represent individuals; Company Pages represent businesses. Best practice uses both — employees build personal brands that give the company human reach, while the Company Page serves as the official brand hub. Employee posts typically reach 3-10x the audience of Company Page posts due to LinkedIn's algorithm favouring individual voices.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How often should a LinkedIn Company Page post?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>LinkedIn data shows companies posting weekly see 5.6x more follower growth than those posting monthly. For most companies, 3-5 posts per week is the optimal cadence. Quality matters more than volume — 3 strong posts outperform 10 weak ones every time.</p></div></div>
